Dan's Music Studio Website
Date Created: December 5th, 2013

Info
-----
This is small web application developed for a pretty cool music studio in West Orange, New Jersey. Check out their original site at 'http://dansbands.wix.com/dms#!'(note: you might need Adobe Flash installed to view the site). 

Specifications
--------------
- Python 2.7 
- Django 1.6
- Bootstrap (www.getbootstrap.com)
- MongoDB 2.4.8

Adding this project to your computer
------------------------------------
1) Install Git:
	Command: $ sudo apt-get install git 

2) Create directory to hold the project, we will can call it 'myproject'

3) go into 'myproject' directory

4) Fork the repo at 'https://github.com/kennychong89/Dan-Music-Studio.git':
	Command: $ git clone https://github.com/kennychong89/Dan-Music-Studio.git

Running this project
--------------------
1) Install VirtualEnvironment for Python (Recommended)
   Info about installation: https://pypi.python.org/pypi/virtualenv
	
   For Linux Users: 
	1) Install pip (http://www.pip-installer.org/en/latest/):
	    
	    (For Debian and Ubuntu Dist): $ sudo apt-get install python-pip
	    (For Fedora Dist): $ sudo yum install python-pip
	    (Other Dist): Check link above

	2) Install VirtualEnvironment:
		Command: $ sudo pip install virtualenv

	3) Create a VirtualEnvironment in 'myproject' directory:
		Command: $ virtualenv myproject/venv
	
	4) Activate your VirtualEnvironment:
		Command: $ . venv/bin/activate

2) Install Django
	1a) With VirtualEnviroment activated:
		Command: $ pip install Django
	
	1b) System-wide installation (with pip installed):
		Command: $ pip install Django 

3) Install MongoDB 2.4.8
	(Check back later)

4) Go into the repository you forked above and find the file 'Manage.py'

5) Run the command: $ python manage.py runserver

6) If there is no error, go to your web browser and enter the address: localhost:8082

7) You should see a welcome screen.

